              <tr>
                <td bgcolor="#ECECEC" valign="top" width="100" nowrap><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2"><b>Wudiskar</b></font></td>
                <td bgcolor="#ECECEC" valign="top" width="100%"><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;05/09/2003&nbsp;: 08:33:41 AM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> After many deaths, many attempts, many different 'tweaks' I think I've got a good method REALLY figured out.<br /><br />basically, slow Drusella, snare her, feign, wait for reset.<br /><br />Now detailed:<br /><br />my spell lineup:<br />self buffed with Shield of Maelin and Force shield, and I have Child of Bertox up.<br />1. Embracing Darkness<br />2. Touch of Mujaki<br />3. Shackle of Spirit<br />4. Saryns Kiss<br />5. Destroy Undead<br />6. Death Peace<br />7. Root<br />8. Force Shield<br /><br />- clear the 2 pats. Use a pet, you'll need him for the Drusella pull, might as well use to kill pats :)<br /><br />- from the corner facing the door to Drusella, you'll want to step forward about 2 'blocks' and do /pet guard there. Positioning of pet important.<br /><br />- Target Drusella, wait for her to path in middle so you can cast Shackle of Spirit on her. <br /><br />* You will want to be standing just a little in front of your pet when you cast, so that you are in spell cast range but not very close to the door and golems.<br /><br />*RARELY the skeleton that stands off to the right side inside the room will path down by Drusella (at far end of room), just kinda watch for it and wait for it to NOT be down by Drusella.<br /><br />- Drusella and all the golems come running. IMMEDIATELY, hit escape (to clear target), start backpeddaling, and hit f8 to target nearest golem, and hit /pet attack.<br /><br />* You are back against the wall now (facing door to Drusella's room), with pet beating on the 4 golems (and vice versa). <br /><br />- get Drusella targeted IMMEDIATELY! (I cheat, I 2 box, and have a rogue opening door for me to target Drusella, then just /assist Woodash). I'd suggest having a special hotkey, /target Drusella and cast dark on next line of hotkey.<br /><br />Cast Dark on Drusella 'right there' (meaning you haven't moved from facing Drusella's door yet). If you get interrupted or resisted you should have time to cast again. (I use a Ceramic Skull of Decay to cut casting time)<br /><br />* At this time your pet should be getting low on health and enraging, and Drusella should be close to you and casting on you.<br /><br />- Turn right and head about halfway to 2/3rds down the hall and FEIGN. If you get hit by Drusella's spell FEIGN again Immediately, and then you should be safe.<br /><br />Here's what should be happening at this time:<br />Drusella is PISSED at you, and has casted, but you've feigned. The pet right behind her is at enrage health, and she turns on it to help finish it off.<br /><br />NOW, let the golems FULLY reset. I am EXTRA carefull with this to be safe. when Dark hits, I glance at my clock, and start ticking off 2 minutes. I do NOT stand up until that 2 minutes has almost completely passed. The golems take a good minute, sometimes as much as a minute and a half to reset.<br /><br />Stand up, nuke her pet, then burn her down!<br /><br />You won't get a clean pull 'every' time with this method, but it should be a pretty high percentage.<br /><br />If anyone else who uses this method with good success has anything to add, please do! :)</span></font></td>
              </tr>
